data.description: Almost new, corner lot, rambler-style living... all less than five minutes from the heart of downtown? Check out 1601 Rampart Drive while you can! Constructed in 2021, this like-new residence includes four bedrooms, three baths and approximately 2,800 square feet of living space. It is tucked on a corner lot in the Fredericksburg Park community. With this location, the Downtown Fredericksburg lifestyle and access is all yours. One of the current owners’ favorite aspects of the home is the bike trail that runs right next to the community as well as direct access to Alum Springs Park! Otherwise, the Fredericksburg VRE, Caroline Street shopping/strolling, the University of Mary Washington and I-95 access (Route 3) are all within five minutes. Dining, grocery and entertainment options aplenty await in Cosner’s Corner and along Route 3 within 10 minutes as well. Zooming in on the homesite, the residence includes a fenced-in back yard anchored by a stamped concrete patio (put in early this year!). Off the main level, there is a covered composite deck for all of your entertaining endeavors. Out front, a concrete driveway leads to the home’s two-car garage. The home itself is light gray with blue shutters and a light blue-gray door. There are solar panels on the roof! Heading inside, this is open, contemporary bliss in its prime, as natural light and light gray luxury vinyl plank flooring abound. All of the carpet in the home is brand new! The home follows Ryan Homes’ prized Bramante floor plan. To the right of the entry foyer, you’ll find two carpeted bedrooms and a full bath, complete with a tub/shower combo, single sink and laminate flooring. To the left of the entry is access to the garage and basement (more on that in a bit!). Continuing, the main area includes the open dining room, living room and kitchen. The kitchen includes a spacious island with room for four seats; light gray cabinetry; white quartz countertops; and stainless-steel appliances (built-in wall oven, gas cooktop and more!). The living area has a gas fireplace and two big windows. The dining space has sliding glass door access to the covered deck. As for the primary bedroom, it is carpeted with windows looking out to the back yard space. It includes tray ceilings, a walk-in closet and ensuite bath complete with a double sink, tiled flooring and spacious stand-up showers. For convenience, the laundry room is right off the primary suite. Heading to the basement, you’re greeted with a huge open recreation room. The flooring was recently updated to a light gray luxury vinyl plank. Other highlights include the home’s final bedroom (long with a sitting area!) and full bath, with a walk-in shower and vanity. Off the bathroom is an unfinished storage and utility area – as you’d expect, the HVAC and hot water heater are running like-new. Systems-wise, the residence also includes a Nest thermostat and select camera components. Your open, rambler-style paradise awaits at 1601 Rampart Drive!
